## 🧠 CLAUDE-MEM Workflow

```
Before implementing:
1. Search claude-mem for similar solutions
2. Check if solution exists
3. Use existing approach

After solving:
1. Save to claude-mem
2. Include context and code snippet
3. Make searchable
```

---

## 🔄 GIT FLOW MASTER

### Commit Format

```
TYPE: PROJECT_NAME - vX.Y.Z

- Change 1
- Change 2
```

### Types

| Type | SemVer | Usage |
|------|--------|-------|
| RELEASE | MAJOR | Breaking changes |
| UPDATE | MINOR | New features |
| PATCH | PATCH | Bug fixes |

### Pre-Commit Workflow

```bash
# Quality Gates
npm run lint
npm run typecheck
npm test

# Commit
TYPE: PROJECT - vX.Y.Z
- Description
```

---

## 🌐 CHROME DEVTOOLS

### UI Debugging Workflow

```bash
1. list_pages → See open pages
2. select_page → Choose page
3. navigate_page → Go to URL
4. take_snapshot → Get page structure
5. list_console_messages → Check errors
6. take_screenshot → Visual check
```

---

## 📖 WEB DOCS WORKFLOW

### Verification (Post-2024 Libraries)

```bash
1. web-search-prime → Find latest docs
2. web-reader → Read full documentation
3. Check breaking changes
4. Test examples in isolation
```

---

## ✅ Pre-Action Checklist

### Before Implementing

- [ ] Search claude-mem for similar implementations
- [ ] Check for existing reusable components
- [ ] Consider delete-first approach
- [ ] Verify patterns in project

### Before Committing

- [ ] Run quality gates
- [ ] Format commit message properly
- [ ] Check for secrets in changes

